{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778286290,"nonce":"dC5CRimK6RMeOzZ87j8Wq8uu80U=","title":"RunPod runbook: sed pattern in §4d eats prefix, breaks pyproject.toml + uv.lock","message":"## Problem\n\nThe path-patch sed commands in CLAUDE.md §4d of the RunPod runbook use a greedy pattern that eats the entire line prefix:\n\n```\nsed -i \"s|.*/feedbax[^\\\"]*|/workspace/feedbax|g\" /workspace/rlrmp/pyproject.toml\n```\n\nThe `.*/feedbax[^\"]*` matches greedily from the start of the line up through `/feedbax` plus any non-quote characters, which means it consumes:\n- The `path = \"` prefix in pyproject.toml\n- The `source = { editable = \"` and `{ name = \"...\", editable = \"` prefixes in uv.lock\n\nResult is a broken file with lines like:\n```\n/workspace/feedbax\"\n```\n\ninstead of:\n```\npath = \"/workspace/feedbax\"\n```\n\nEncountered during 2026-05-08 baseline-jerk-vrnn-matrix deploy on a resumed 5090 pod. The TOML is then invalid; would have caused a downstream import failure if the existing venv hadnt already been working.\n\n## Fix\n\nUse a pattern that only replaces the path content INSIDE the quotes, preserving whatever prefix is there:\n\n```\nsed -i \"s|\\\"[^\\\"]*/feedbax[^\\\"]*\\\"|\\\"/workspace/feedbax\\\"|g\" /workspace/rlrmp/pyproject.toml /workspace/rlrmp/uv.lock\nsed -i \"s|\\\"[^\\\"]*/jax.cookbook[^\\\"]*\\\"|\\\"/workspace/jax-cookbook\\\"|g\" /workspace/rlrmp/uv.lock /workspace/feedbax/pyproject.toml /workspace/feedbax/uv.lock\n```\n\nVerified working on the 2026-05-08 deploy after re-rsyncing to restore the broken files.\n\n## Action\n\nUpdate CLAUDE.md §4d with the corrected sed patterns. Consider also adding a verification step (\"grep editable /workspace/rlrmp/uv.lock should show /workspace/feedbax intact\").","files":null}]}